	Nissan Trading Corportation - Products and Services































 




Nissan Trading About Nissan Trading Expand About Nissan Trading Products and Services Nissan Trading Worldwide EDI Specifications Supplier Quality Manual


















Products and Services





The following products and services are offered by Nissan Trading Corporation Americas.



Warehousing & Distribution



Warehousing is a serious expense.  Let us utilize our warehouses to store and ship your product for you.   We also offer repackaging services, Kitting, De-Kitting, and export packaging services.



Automotive Components Business



Along with supplying domestic Nissan plants and affiliated component makers with parts and materials from overseas, the Automotive Components Business also exports components to Nissan's overseas facilities.  From product development to final delivery, the business' diverse management capabilities enable it to provide invaluable support to the range of clients it proudly serves.



Machinery Business



The Machinery Business imports, exports and distributes within Japan a diverse range of machines from manufacturing, assembly and processing machinery to various types of robots and electronically controlled machines.  The Machinery Business provides technical assistance to manufacturers through every stage of the purchase of new machinery, from the identification of customer needs to installing and ensuring full operation of all machinery.



Chemicals Business



The Chemicals Business handles a diverse range of products including organic and inorganic chemicals, petrochemicals, high performance and new materials and alloys for the aerospace industry.  The Chemicals Business endeavors to develop and supply materials that meet the individual specifications of customers.



Energy and Materials Business



The Energy and Materials Business supports distribution and manufacturing industries through the supply of fuel to factories in Japan and to cargo ships and tankers at major ports worldwide.  The Energy and Materials Business also manages a gasoline card system that allows the staff of Nissan and its affiliates to purchase fuel and the have the cost deducted from their monthly salary.  The business boasts a comprehensive range of fuels and related products, including petroleum products for general consumers and coke used in the casting process.



Steel Business



As a designated supplier of products from the major steel mills, the Steel Business distributes steel, special steel and steel alloys.  Through its affiliated secondary processing companies, the Steel Business is able to tailor products to meet the exact needs of clients.  The business also handles technologically advanced materials, such as new steel alloys.



Vehicles Group



Through its export activities, the Vehicles Group is expanding the sales of Nissan vehicles in South and Central America, Asia, Africa, and the rest of the world.  The group also imports vehicles and accessories and oversees the shipment of non-Japanese-made vehicles to other countries.



Non-Ferrous Metals Business



Aluminum alloys are increasingly gaining importance in vehicle manufacturing.  The Non-Ferrous Metals Business supplies these products in the form of panels, rods and ingots, and also handles a variety of precious metals.  The automotive industry is making greater efforts to use and recycle these metals and other raw materials, reflecting the community's concern for the world's limited resources.


















JIT Plant Deliveries
Machinery/Chemical
